More specifically, the transformation follows these steps:
A "MIME-Version" header field is added, as described in .
A "Content-Type" header field is added, also as described in . The media type is "multipart/mixed". A unique compliant boundary is also generated.
Two MIME parts are created. The first MIME part is of type "text/plain", and contains the body of the original message. The second MIME part contains whatever content the Mediator is configured to add, and uses a media type appropriate to that content.
The body of the message is replaced with the following, in a manner compliant with , namely:
the boundary;
an optional "Content-Type" header field indicating the original content used the default "text/plain" media type, and the optional "charset" parameter;
a line break;
the body of the original message;
a line break;
the boundary;
any MIME header fields needed to introduce the content the Mediator wishes to add;
a line break;
the Mediator's content;
the terminating boundary.

 More specifically, the transformation follows these
		    steps:


			 Remove the Content-Type header field from the
