				 the new boundary; 

				 the previously deleted Content-Type
				    header field; 

				 a line break; 

				 the entire original content of the
				    message; 

				 a line break; 

				 the new boundary; 

				 any MIME header fields needed
				    to introduce the content the Mediator
				    wishes to add; 

				 a line break; 

				 the Mediator's content; 

				 the terminating instance of the new
				    boundary.

Entries in this registry include all of the following:
A simple name for a reversible message transformation;
A terse description for the transformation;
A reference to a stable specification in which this transformation and its inverse are clearly described;
Must be one of:
"active", meaning the transformation is in current use;
"deprecated", meaning the transformation is not in current use.
